### TITLE ###
LambdaInheritsEnclosingNarrowing
### DESCRIPTION ###
A lambda defined under a narrowed enclosing scope inherits the
narrowed type for captured variables. (Closure-rule caveat noted
in synthLambda doc - future Pyright-style reassignment-after-
definition tracking will tighten this.)
### INPUT ###
fn f(x: int?):
    if x != null:
        cb = fn():
            y = x
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  x @ 2:8 -> int?
  cb @ 3:9 -> <no-type>
  y @ 4:13 -> <no-type>
  x @ 4:17 -> int

# Symbol types
  cb (local): fn() -> void
  f (fn): fn(int?) -> void
  x (param): int?
  y (local): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
LambdaBodyNarrowingDoesNotLeakOut
### DESCRIPTION ###
Narrowings inside the lambda body shouldn't leak back to the
enclosing scope (tc.frame is restored after the lambda walk).
### INPUT ###
fn f(x: int?):
    cb = fn():
        if x != null:
            a = x
    z = x
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  cb @ 2:5 -> <no-type>
  x @ 3:12 -> int?
  a @ 4:13 -> <no-type>
  x @ 4:17 -> int
  z @ 5:5 -> <no-type>
  x @ 5:9 -> int?

# Symbol types
  a (local): int
  cb (local): fn() -> void
  f (fn): fn(int?) -> void
  x (param): int?
  z (local): int?

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
RecursiveLambdaTupleReturnCollapsesNeverArm
### DESCRIPTION ###
A recursive lambda's inferred return type used to surface
`int|[never, int]` - the recursive arm synth'd to `[never, int]`
(self_call's return was still being inferred, so it slot was
Never). Tuples with any Never position are uninhabited, so the
union join drops them; the final type is `int`.
### INPUT ###
self_call = fn(n: int):
    if n <= 0:
        return 1
    return self_call(n-1), 2

x: int = self_call(5)
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  self_call @ 1:1 -> <no-type>
  n @ 2:8 -> int
  self_call @ 4:12 -> fn(int) -> never
  n @ 4:22 -> int
  x @ 6:1 -> <no-type>
  self_call @ 6:10 -> fn(int) -> int

# Symbol types
  n (param): int
  self_call (local): fn(int) -> int
  x (local): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
### TITLE ###
RecursiveLambdaScalarBaseCaseStillWorks
### DESCRIPTION ###
Regression lock for the scalar case the collapse already
covered before tuples: a recursive lambda whose recursive arm
is just `self_call(n-1)` (bare Never during inference) returns
the base case's type, not `int|never`.
### INPUT ###
self_call = fn(n: int) -> int:
    if n <= 0:
        return 1
    return self_call(n-1)

x: int = self_call(5)
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  self_call @ 1:1 -> <no-type>
  n @ 2:8 -> int
  self_call @ 4:12 -> fn(int) -> never
  n @ 4:22 -> int
  x @ 6:1 -> <no-type>
  self_call @ 6:10 -> fn(int) -> int

# Symbol types
  n (param): int
  self_call (local): fn(int) -> int
  x (local): int

# Diagnostics
  (none)
